# Request a global body plan that respects pose-based collision constraints
# from other robots' plans. Used by the conflict_based_search node when
# servicing per-robot replan requests.
#
# Each constrained pose is treated as a forbidden region: the returned plan's
# body must not overlap (oriented-bounding-box test) any constrained pose.
# An empty constraint set is the same as a normal "plan from current state to
# current goal" request.

quad_msgs/RobotPlanConstraints constraints

# When true the planner is permitted to warm-start from the trees it built on
# the previous request (lazy-pruning vertices that violate the new
# constraints). When false the planner builds new RRT-Connect trees from
# scratch — this matches the original ROS1 behavior.
bool warm_start

---

quad_msgs/RobotPlan plan
float64 path_length
bool success
